                                "start": 0,
                                "stop": 7.797,
                                "byte_start": 106496,
                                "byte_stop": 137738,
                                "text": "Justice Breyer has the opinion of the Court this morning in case 07-610, Locke versus Karass."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 7.797,
                        "stop": 160.056,
                        "byte_start": 137738,
                        "byte_stop": 746705,
                        "speaker": {
                            "ID": 15139,
                            "name": "Stephen G. Breyer",
                            "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/people\/stephen_g_breyer",
                            "last_name": "Breyer",
                            "roles": [
                                {
                                    "id": 2785,
                                    "type": "scotus_justice",
                                    "date_start": 775890000,
                                    "date_end": 0,
                                    "appointing_president": "Bill Clinton",
                                    "role_title": "Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/preson_role\/scotus_justice\/2785"
                                }
                            ],
                            "thumbnail": {
                                "id": 32682,
                                "mime": "image\/png",
                                "size": 49908,
                                "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/sites\/default\/files\/stephen_g_breyer_0.png"
                            },
                            "length_of_service": 7777,
                            "identifier": "stephen_g_breyer"
                        },
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 7.797,
                                "stop": 29.14,
                                "byte_start": 137738,
                                "byte_stop": 223107,
                                "text": "Under Maine state law, like a lot of state laws, if a government employee disagrees with and does not belong to the local union that represents that employee and all the others in the workplace, then the one who disagrees still has to pay the union something, a service fee instead of the union dues."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 29.14,
                                "stop": 40.508,
                                "byte_start": 223107,
                                "byte_stop": 268560,
                                "text": "Now this Court has long held in principle that although there are certain exceptions, Government may require this kind of a payment without violating the First Amendment."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 40.508,
                                "stop": 43.633,
                                "byte_start": 268560,
                                "byte_stop": 281098,
                                "text": "It\u0027s not quite voluntary but still they can pay."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 43.633,
                                "stop": 46.167,
                                "byte_start": 281098,
                                "byte_stop": 291234,
                                "text": "The union can charge them."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 46.167,
                                "stop": 53.424,
                                "byte_start": 291234,
                                "byte_stop": 320282,
                                "text": "Now in this case, which is a kind of question I find that draw that line between what they can and cannot charge."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 53.424,
                                "stop": 63.582,
                                "byte_start": 320282,
                                "byte_stop": 360929,
                                "text": "A local union charges the nonmembers a service fee that among other things reflects an affiliation fee that the local pays the national."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 63.582,
                                "stop": 73.573,
                                "byte_start": 360929,
                                "byte_stop": 400844,
                                "text": "Now that affiliation fee that all the locals pay the national in turn has a component that the national uses in order to pay its lawyers."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 73.573,
                                "stop": 92.847,
                                "byte_start": 400844,
                                "byte_stop": 477957,
                                "text": "So the question is whether, the local, when it charges the nonmembers their pro rata share of the dues, whether it can include a pro rata share of that part of the fee it\u0027s going to pay the national that goes to paying the national\u0027s lawyers\u0027 litigation expenses."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 92.847,
                                "stop": 94.387,
                                "byte_start": 477957,
                                "byte_stop": 484122,
                                "text": "That\u0027s the question."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 94.387,
                                "stop": 97.845,
                                "byte_start": 484122,
                                "byte_stop": 497915,
                                "text": "And the answer to the question in our view is yes, it can."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 97.845,
                                "stop": 100.518,
                                "byte_start": 497915,
                                "byte_stop": 508573,
                                "text": "And there are two conditions."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 100.518,
                                "stop": 113.971,
                                "byte_start": 508573,
                                "byte_stop": 562385,
                                "text": "First, it has to be that litigation that the national is involved in has to be the subject matter, has to be the kind that would be chargeable if local litigation by unions were at issue."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 113.971,
                                "stop": 122.818,
                                "byte_start": 562385,
                                "byte_stop": 597807,
                                "text": "And second, the litigation involved, that kind of obligation that charged for the national, it has to be reciprocal in nature."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 122.818,
                                "stop": 134.968,
                                "byte_start": 597807,
                                "byte_stop": 646395,
                                "text": "So the local that gives the money to the national has to expect that other locals will contribute to its problems that need to be resolved by litigation just as it is now contributing to the others."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 134.968,
                                "stop": 147.692,
                                "byte_start": 646395,
                                "byte_stop": 697281,
                                "text": "But where those two things are concerned, subject matter is right and there is reciprocity, then the union can charge the nonmembers that money and our opinion explains why all that is so."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 147.692,
                                "stop": 151.593,
                                "byte_start": 697281,
                                "byte_stop": 712955,
                                "text": "And we affirm the Court of Appeals\u0027 decision which reached a similar conclusion."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 151.593,
                                "stop": 153.436,
                                "byte_start": 712955,
                                "byte_stop": 720269,
                                "text": "Our decision is unanimous."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 153.436,
                                "stop": 160.056,
                                "byte_start": 720269,
                                "byte_stop": 746705,
                                "text": "Justice Alito has filed the concurring opinion which the Chief Justice and Justice Scalia have joined."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
